\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Yes, every available pole and monument was used for the purpose, and also every available tree. In particular did the Istorichesky Prospekt become richly garnished with wind-swayed corpses; and the same with the Nakhimovsky Prospekt, Ekaterinskaya Street, Bolshaya-Morskaya Street, and the Primorsky Boulevard. Previously Commandant Bothmer, the lieutenant of the German contingent hitherto in occupation of the Crimea, had ordered the population not to make any complaints against the Soviet\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s officials, \u8220\'93since such complaints only help the White Guards in their resistance.\u8221\'94 And such was the orgy of madness and slaughter as to include even shootings of sick and wounded from the hospitals\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 of a batch of 272 persons from the\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Zemstvo\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~sanatorium at}{ -}
