\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Russian society was not one before the revolution. The confrontation between peasants and "landowners", non-resident and Cossacks, workers and "breeders", tops and intellectuals, and the national question, all this happened, and then "exploded." And there was also the First World War, which "accustomed" to the ordinariness of death and violence. There was a willingness to accept violence, and it was accepted by the parties towards their opponents. Therefore, the mythologization of the red terror is its consideration in isolation from the white terror, from social and other reasons.}{ }
